(secondQuint)Young Blind Child Melatonin Treatment Study.

 Subjects will complete 25-hours of hourly salivary, plasma sampling biweekly.

 Melatonin will be measured in urine, for children under the age of 3.

 Sleep and behavioral questionnaires will be completed by parents and/or teachers.

 This study involves an optional, 1-year melatonin treatment sub-study, in which the children will take 0.

1 - 3mg daily.

 A second optional sub-study involves a study of the child's sleep through polysomnography, in order to identify possible sleep disorders.

